q^0=\dfrac{q^1-1}{q-1}\implies1=1
P(1)
P(2)
q^0+q^1=\dfrac{q^2-1}{q-1}\implies1+q=1+q
P(2)
P(k+1):1+q+...+q^{k-1}+q^{k}=\dfrac{q^{k+1}-1}{q-1}
 \frac{q^k-1}{q-1}+q^k=\frac{q^{k+1}-1}{q-1} 
k
k+1
1+q+...+q^{k}+q^{k+1}=\frac{q^{k+1}-1}{q-1}+q^{k+1}=\frac{q^{k+1}-1+q^{k+1}(q-1)}{q-1}=\frac{q^{k+1}-1+q^{k+2}-q^{k+1}}{q-1}=\frac{q^{k+1}-1}{q-1}
\frac{q^k-1}{q-1} + q^k = \frac{q^k-1 + (q-1)q^k}{q-1} = \frac{q^{k+1} + q^k - q^k - 1}{q-1} = \frac{q^{k+1}-1}{q-1}
